mizarlabs.transformers.technical package¶

mizarlabs.transformers.technical.factory module¶

class mizarlabs.transformers.technical.factory.TAFactory[source]¶

Bases: object

Factory that creates sklearn transformers for function available in the TA-lib package.

create_transformer(func_name: str, col_to_transform: Optional[Union[List[str], str]] = None, col_to_transform_mapping: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None, kw_args: Optional[dict] = None) → sklearn.preprocessing._function_transformer.FunctionTransformer[source]¶

Creates a transformer for a given function available in the TA-lib package.

Parameters

  • func_name (str) – name of function in TA-lib package

  • col_to_transform (Union[List[str], str], optional) – name of the column in dataframe to transform, defaults to None

  • col_to_transform_mapping (Dict[str, str], optional) – remapping of names in dataframe to valid arg names in the TA function, defaults to None

  • kw_args (dict, optional) – kwargs for the TA function, defaults to None

Raises

  • TypeError – transformer only works on pandas DataFrames

  • ValueError – transformer expect certain columns to be available in the dataframe to transform

Returns

scikit-learn FunctionTransformer version of the TA function

Return type

FunctionTransformer

Returns

class mizarlabs.transformers.technical.moving_average.MovingAverageCrossOver(fast: int, slow: int, column_name: str, fill_between_crossovers: bool = False)[source]¶

Bases: sklearn.base.BaseEstimator, sklearn.base.TransformerMixin

Moving average crossover transformer

It transform the input data to a 1 when the the fast moving average goes above the slow moving average and -1 when the slow moving average goes above the fast moving average. When fill_between_crossovers is true, then the transfromation will be equal to 1 when the fast moving average is above the slow one and -1 viceversa.

The transformer is specified by the fast and slow moving average number of bars.

Parameters

  • fast (int) – number of bars to use for the moving average of the fast moving average

  • slow (int) – number of bars to use for the moving average of the slow moving average

  • column_name (str) – The name of the column in input that will be used for the transformation.

  • fill_between_crossovers (bool) – whether or not to fill the crossover value untill the next crossover.
